Drama unfolded in Pinetown,Durban on Saturday when armed men robbed a local bank Four armed men, posing as private security guards, robbed a bank outside Durban on Saturday. It is understood that the men hijacked security guards and robbed them off their uniforms before heading to a bank in the Pinetown area, west of the city. Police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said:“This morning at 8.15am four suspects wearing security guard uniforms entered the bank and took an undisclosed amount of cash before they fled the scene. “No one was injured and no shots were fired.” Zwane said police were at the scene gathering information.